        <updateDate>2007-05-24T18:00:51Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>College Saver's Credit Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) allow certain middle-income individual taxpayers age 18 or older a refundable tax credit for 50% of their contributions to a qualified tuition program (tax-exempt college savings plan), up to an annual limit of $2,000; and (2) require the distribution of financial education materials to participants in a qualified tuition program.</p><p>Requires the Secretary of the Treasury to study and report to Congress on the participation of individuals in qualified tuition programs. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
